init_text:
A woman has been dating guy after guy, but it never seems to work out. She’s unaware that she’s actually been dating the same guy over and over; a shapeshifter who’s fallen for her, and is certain he’s going to get it right this time.

One day,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: meets a man who seems perfect for her, but she can’t stop thinking about the shapeshifter.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Then, one day, she meets a man who seems perfect for her.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She can’t stop wondering if it’s her.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She wonders if she’s the problem.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Helena realizes she is going to have to put her life on pause and step back to figure out what’s wrong.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If she can’t fix herself, how will she find the right man for her?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: As Helena looks back on her relationships, she realizes that there is a pattern to her problem.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She says to herself, "Oh my goodness.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I am dating the same guy over and over again.”

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Suddenly, she has the key to her problem.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She can see it so clearly.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She realizes that the problem is her.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She has a fear of trusting her heart and letting another person in.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She’s afraid that he will hurt her and not love her back like she loves him.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Helena realizes it’s time for her to open herself up and trust again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She has to let a man in emotionally and, for the first time, be vulnerable.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She has to learn to love herself before she can let anyone else in and be happy.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Helena thinks, "I have been so scared that I’m going to get hurt.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I am afraid to let myself feel.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It’s time to wake up and let someone love me the way I love them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I’ve got to be strong and brave.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She lets her guard down and feels the first stirrings of a love she never thought possible.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: As Helena feels love again, she knows she has finally found someone to trust and be vulnerable with.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: As she allows her heart to open, she is filled with hope and excited for what the future holds.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She knows she has finally found the right man to love and be loved by.
